Parliament, Wednesday, 28 November 2018  The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will this afternoon hold a hearing with the Department of Water Affairs and Sanitation on irregular, fruitless, wasteful expenditure, as well as accruals and commitments. The hearing will also be on project overruns, unauthorised expenditure, projects not budgeted for or projects not funded and the overdraft at the Reserve Bank. Details of meeting: Date:               Wednesday, 28 November 2018 Time:              18:00 Venue:            Committee Room V454, 4th Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the committees Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
	Email: fndenze@parliament.gov.za The Constitution says a parliamentary committee meeting may not be closed to the public “unless it is reasonable and justifiable to do so in an open and democratic society”.Read more